dsDescriptionValue.value:
Data are presented for all farms and for all farms with sales of $10,000 or more. Data include number of farms, land in farms, size of farms, value of land and buildings, value of machinery and equipment, characteristics of operator, selected production expenses, total crop land, irrigation of farm land, value of agriculture products sold, inventory and sale of livestock and poultry, and major crops harvested.

Data are available for each State and for each county.

fields.value: Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Universe: The universe is all farms. A farm is any place from which $1,000 or more of agricultural products were sold, or normally would have been sold, during the census year.;Type: ODUM:ACCESS.CATEGORY Notes: I;
